1	//! R2 tests — rule rendering.
2	//!
3	//! Two layers:
4	//!  1. Probe-pinned unit tests: hand-written `Rule` fixtures asserted against
5	//!     byte-exact oracle output (probe captures under
6	//!     workspace/scratchpad/probes/, provenance `probe:<name>`).
7	//!  2. Whole-rule-block parity over the round-2 curated corpus captures
8	//!     (round2/targets/*.hs.txt): every rule block of every file is parsed
9	//!     back into the crate's AST by a layout-insensitive echo-parser (test
10	//!     harness only — it discards all whitespace, so layout can only come
11	//!     from the renderer) and re-rendered; the bytes must match the capture.
